<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-3657] D TFileWriterTransport close should use non-priority send</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3657</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;prioritySend is used in TFileWriterTransport close method.&lt;br/&gt;
A possible problem with this is that even synchronized calls that are strictly before close call can be ignored in rare occasions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The author has put a comment &quot;FIXME: Should use normal send here&quot; and there&apos;s no reason not to.&lt;br/&gt;
I suspect it is a remnant of old implementation or local debug stuff.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
